        <prj:name>Science Goal</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We observe HCN and HCO+ 4-3, CS 7-6 and CO 3-2 in Band7. 
HCN 4-3, HCO+ 4-3 and CS 7-6 will provide valuable information about the excitation of this molecule combined with the HCN 1-0, HCO+ 1-0 and CS 2-1 detection in Band 3, respectively. 
Comparisons among these dense gas tracers are useful to constrain the excitation mechanism of molecular gas, e.g., X-ray radiation heating, in the CND and nuclear ring. 
We investigate the inflow mass from the nuclear ring and kinematic energy of the outflow from CO 3-2 data.</prj:note>
