        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Technical Justification
Requested sensitivity: 
We aim to have a spatial resolution of 0.25″, corresponding to 21 pc at the distance of NGC 613. The main-beam temperature of HCN 4-3 toward the center of NGC 613 with ASTE (HPBW~22″) is Tmb &gt; 0.02 K (figure 3). It is clear from figure 4 that the temperature of CO 3-2 is higher than it of HCN 4-3. Tmb of HCO+ 4-3 detected with ASTE is almost equivalent with it of HCN although not shown in figure 3. Given the consistency between distribution of HCN 4-3 corresponds to that of H2 1-0 S(1) (figure 1), it is expected that most of HCN concentrates in a radius of 0.75″from the center (figure 2). We estimate about 4.3 (=0.02*(22/1.5)^2) K for the proposed beam. We therefore need a noise level of 0.72 K at 5 km/s for 6σ detection. We observe in dual polarization to obtain maximum sensitivity. We require total 12-m array time of 40.07 min (2.16 min per field) taking into account fraction of overhead time, and total time for science goal including ACA and TP time of 3.67 hrs, according to Observation Tool for ALMA. In the same setup we will also observe CS 7−6 simultaneously, which will provide valuable information about the excitation of this molecule combined with the CS 2−1 detection in Band 3. Here we assume that CS 7−6 shows the same flux as HCO+, but the Tsys is better in the frequency of CS 7−6 (343 GHz). The integration time is then limited by HCO+ 4−3 line.

Imaging requirements: 
We propose to observe 1 rectangular field of 14″×14″to cover the nuclear ring as well as the circum-nuclear disk of NGC 613. The number of pointing mosaic is 3 for 12-m array with spacing 0.48 of main beam. The declination of NGC 613 is -29d25m06s. Using CASA simulator, it is confirmed that good map is produced owing to good (u, v) coverage.

Correlator setup: 
We observe HCN and HCO+ 4-3, CO 3-2 and CS 7-6 in Band 7. 
We estimate that the velocity widths of spectra are about 350 km/s at most (figure 4).
The bandwidth (velocity width) is set at 937.5 MHz (824 km/s), 468.75 MHz (408 km/s), 1875 MHz (1584 km/s) and 468.75 MHz (398 km/s) for CS 7-6, CO 3-2, HCN 4-3 and HCO+ 4-3, respectively, in order to observe simultaneously. We smooth the lines to 5 km/s to improve signal to noise ratio.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
